===Verb=== {{en-verb|articulat|ing}}
# To make clear or effective. # To speak clearly; to [[enunciate]]. #: ''I wish he’d '''articulate''' his words more clearly.'' # To [[explain]]; to put into words; to make something [[specific]]. #: ''I like this painting, but I can’t '''articulate''' why.'' # To bend or hinge something at intervals, or to allow or build something so that it can bend. #: ''an '''articulated''' bus'' # {{music}} to [[attack]] a [[note]], as by [[tonguing]], [[slur]]ring, [[bow]]ing, etc. #: '''''Articulate''' that passage heavily.'' # {{anatomy}} to form a joint or connect by joints #: ''The lower jaw '''articulates''' with the skull at the temporomandibular joint.''
