** {{audio|en-us-articulate-verb.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# [[clear]], [[effective]]
# especially, [[speak]]ing in a clear or effective manner
#: ''She’s a bright, '''articulate''' young woman.''
# able to [[bend]] or [[hinge]] at certain points or [[interval]]s
#: ''The robot arm was '''articulate''' in two directions.''

====Translations====
{{trans-top|clear, effective}}
* German: {{t+|de|klar}}, {{t+|de|effektiv}}
* Hungarian: {{t|hu|érthető}}, {{t|hu|világos}}
{{trans-mid}}
{{trans-bottom}}

{{trans-top|speaking in a clear or effective manner}}
* German: {{t+|de|redegewandt}}
* Hungarian: {{t-|hu|artikulált}}
{{trans-mid}}
{{trans-bottom}}

{{trans-top|able to bend or hinge at certain points or intervals}}
{{trans-mid}}
{{trans-bottom}}

{{checktrans-top}}
* {{ttbc|Dutch}}: [[welbespraakt]], taalvaardig
* {{ttbc|French}}: [[clair]] (1)
* {{ttbc|Italian}}: [[chiaro]] (1), [[eloquente]] (2)
* {{ttbc|Spanish}}: [[claro]] (1), [[elocuente]] (2)
{{checktrans-bottom}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|articulat|ing}}

# To make clear or effective.
# To speak clearly; to [[enunciate]].
#: ''I wish he’d '''articulate''' his words more clearly.''
# To [[explain]]; to put into words; to make something [[specific]].
#: ''I like this painting, but I can’t '''articulate''' why.''
# To bend or hinge something at intervals, or to allow or build something so that it can bend.
#: ''an '''articulated''' bus''
# {{music}} to [[attack]] a [[note]], as by [[tonguing]], [[slur]]ring, [[bow]]ing, etc.
#: '''''Articulate''' that passage heavily.''
# {{anatomy}} to form a joint or connect by joints
#: ''The lower jaw '''articulates''' with the skull at the temporomandibular joint.''

====Related terms====
* [[articulation]]

