{{wikipedia|Articulation}}

===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|la}} {{term|articulatus|articulātus|lang=la}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{a|UK}} {{enPR|ärtĭ'kyələt}}, {{IPA|/ɑː(ɹ)ˈtɪk.jʊ.lət/}}, {{SAMPA|/A:(r\)"tIk.jU.l@t/}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|ärtĭ'kyələt}}, {{IPA|/ɑːɹˈtɪk.jə.lət/}}, {{SAMPA|/A:r\"tIk.j@.l@t/}}
*: {{audio|en-us-articulate-adj.ogg|Audio (US)}}

====Adjective====
{{en-adj}}

# [[clear]], [[effective]]
# especially, [[speak]]ing in a clear or effective manner
#: ''She’s a bright, '''articulate''' young woman.''
# able to [[bend]] or [[hinge]] at certain points or [[interval]]s
#: ''The robot arm was '''articulate''' in two directions.''

=====Synonyms=====
* {{sense|good at speaking}} [[eloquent]], [[well-spoken]]

=====Translations=====
{{trans-top|clear, effective}}
* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|ясен}},  {{t|bg|отчетлив}}
* Dutch: {{t+|nl|duidelijk}}, {{t+|nl|klaar}}, {{t+|nl|efficiënt}}
* French: {{t+|fr|clair}}
* German: {{t+|de|klar}}, {{t+|de|effektiv}}
{{trans-mid}}
* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|érthető}}, {{t+|hu|világos}}
* Italian: {{t+|it|chiaro}}
* Spanish: {{t+|es|claro}}
{{trans-bottom}}

{{trans-top|speaking in a clear or effective manner}}
* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|членоразделен}}
* Dutch: {{t|nl|welbespraakt}}, {{t|nl|taalvaardig}}
* German: {{t-|de|redegewandt}}
* Hungarian: {{t-|hu|artikulált}}
{{trans-mid}}
* Italian: {{t+|it|eloquente}}
* Russian: {{t|ru|выразительный|tr=vyrazítel’nyj}},  {{t|ru|членораздельный|tr=členorazdél’nyj}}
* [[Scottish Gaelic]]: {{t-|gd|siùbhlach|xs=Scottish Gaelic}}, {{t|gd|pongail}}
* Spanish: {{t-|es|elocuente}}
{{trans-bottom}}

{{trans-top|able to bend or hinge at certain points or intervals}}
* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|ставен}},  {{t|bg|шарнирен}}
{{trans-mid}}
* Dutch: {{t-|nl|geleed}}, {{t-|nl|gelede}}, {{t|nl|geärticuleerd}}
{{trans-bottom}}

===Etymology 2===
From the adjective.

====Pronunciation====
* {{a|UK}} {{enPR|ärtĭ'kyəlāt}}, {{IPA|/ɑː(ɹ)ˈtɪk.jʊ.leɪt/}}, {{SAMPA|/A:(r\)"tIk.jU.leIt/}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|ärtĭ'kyəlāt}}, {{IPA|/ɑːɹˈtɪk.jə.leɪt/}}, {{SAMPA|/A:r\"tIk.j@.leIt/}}
*: {{audio|en-us-articulate-verb.ogg|Audio (US)}}

====Verb====
{{en-verb|articulat|ing}}

# To make clear or effective.
# To speak clearly; to [[enunciate]].
#: ''I wish he’d '''articulate''' his words more clearly.''
# To [[explain]]; to put into words; to make something [[specific]].
#: ''I like this painting, but I can’t '''articulate''' why.''
# To bend or hinge something at intervals, or to allow or build something so that it can bend.
#: ''an '''articulated''' bus''
# {{music}} to [[attack]] a [[note]], as by [[tonguing]], [[slur]]ring, [[bow]]ing, etc.
#: '''''Articulate''' that passage heavily.''
# {{anatomy}} to form a joint or connect by joints
#: ''The lower jaw '''articulates''' with the skull at the temporomandibular joint.''

=====Derived terms=====
* {{l|en|articulable}}

=====Related terms=====
* [[articulation]]

=====Translations=====
